CLIPPERS PLAY MAGIC IN FIRST EXHIBITION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRIS BAKER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Elmore Spencer is expected to start in place of center Stanley Roberts when 
the Clippers open their exhibition season tonight against the Orlando Magic at 
the Orlando Arena. 
</P>
<P>
 Roberts, who hasn't practiced with the team after reporting to training camp 
overweight and out of shape, didn't accompany the team on the trip, which ends 
Saturday with a game against the Atlanta Hawks at the Omni. 
</P>
<P>
 Spencer, who started 63 games after Roberts suffered a torn right Achilles' 
tendon last season, has been hampered by a strained groin during two-a-day 
workouts. CHRIS BAKER 
