<HEADLINE>
<P>
WALLACE LEADS WORKMAN PAST BOLSA GRANDE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JON CLIFFORD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 City of Industry Workman's Charles Wallace ran for 198 yards and scored three 
touchdowns to lead the Lobos to a 27-0 nonleague victory over Bolsa Grande 
Thursday night at La Puente High School. 
</P>
<P>
 Bolsa Grande (1-5) struggled on both sides of the ball and lost its fifth 
consecutive game. 
</P>
<P>
 Wallace got Workman on the board first when, with four minutes left in the 
first quarter, he returned a punt 67 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 The Workman defense held the Matadors to only one first down in their first 
three possessions. 
</P>
<P>
 Workman (1-5) struck again on the second play of the second quarter when 
quarterback Ryan Graham ran a quarterback draw eight yards for a 13-0 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Bolsa Grande's best scoring opportunity followed, when Matador quarterback 
David Prince connected with David Ross on a 46-yard pass to the Lobos' 30-yard 
line. But on first and goal from the six-yard line, Prince fumbled the snap and 
Workman recovered. 
</P>
<P>
 Bolsa Grande's next drive ended when a snap went over Prince's head and 
through the back of the end zone for a safety and a 15-0 Workman halftime lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Wallace finished off the Lobos' second drive of the third quarter, scoring on 
an eight-yard run to give Workman a 21-0 lead. Both teams struggled on offense 
the rest of the game. Workman's Mark Diaz intercepted a Prince pass late in the 
fourth quarter to set up Wallace's final score, a five-yard run with 30 seconds 
remaining. JON CLIFFORD 
</P>
</TEXT>
