<HEADLINE>
<P>
PACIFIC COAST LEAGUE FOOTBALL; HIGHFIELD, MAHONEY HELP UNIVERSITY SHUT OUT 
ESTANCIA, 20-0 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jarrett Mahoney's 35-yard touchdown run midway through the first quarter 
helped University defeat Estancia, 20-0, in a Pacific Coast League opener 
Thursday night at Irvine High. 
</P>
<P>
 Mahoney carried only four times, rushing for 39 yards for University (3-3, 
1-0).Estancia (3-3, 0-1) was led by Karlo Amaya, who rushed for 77 yards in 11 
carries. 
</P>
<P>
 It looked as if Estancia would tie the score when Amaya raced for 45 yards for 
a touchdown early in the second quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 But touchdown was negated when the Eagles were called for clipping. The drive 
ended when University's Ray Davis tackled quarterback Frough Jahid for a 
10-yard loss at the Trojans' 36-yard line. 
</P>
<P>
 University broke open the game when Tucker Highfield scored from one yard with 
7:48 remaining in the game. The kick failed. 
</P>
<P>
 Highfield was the game's leading rusher with 105 yards in 13 carries. 
</P>
<P>
 University's defense accounted for the other score. Cornerback Bryant Geary 
intercepted a pass by backup quarterback Jack Clark and returned it 80 yards 
for a touchdown to put the Trojans ahead, 20-0, with 15 seconds remaining. 
</P>
<P>
 University's quarterback Alan Price attempted only three passes, completing 
one for seven yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Jahid completed five of 15 passes for 65 yards for Estancia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
