<HEADLINE>
<P>
CROSS-COUNTRY CHAMPIONSHIPS ARE SCHEDULED FOR SATURDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MATT FARMER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Capistrano Valley's Adalberto Sanchez will be the cross-country runner to beat 
during Saturday's Orange County Championships at Irvine Regional Park, but the 
boys' competition figures to be highlighted by another matchup between Katella 
and Santa Ana. 
</P>
<P>
 Katella, ranked No. 1 in the county, will try to regain the meet's Division I 
title, which it lost last year to Santa Ana.The Knights defeated the No. 2 
Saints, 69-75, last weekend at the Central Park Invitational. 
</P>
<P>
 Century League powers Orange (No. 3), Santa Ana Valley (No. 4), Villa Park 
(No. 5) and El Modena (No. 6) also will chase the county title. 
</P>
<P>
 Sanchez, who finished third at last year's meet, should receive his main 
competition from Newport Harbor's Shahram DeZahd, Santa Ana Valley's Joel 
Orozco and La Habra's Chuck Gatchell. 
</P>
<P>
 The girls' competition matches top-ranked Esperanza and No. 4 Edison from the 
Sunset League and Irvine (No. 2), El Toro (No. 3) and Corona del Mar (No. 6) 
from the Sea View League. 
</P>
<P>
 Competition begins at 8 a.m., with the top 13 seeded girls' teams racing for 
the county title at 9 and the top 12 seeded boys' teams squaring off at 10:24. 
The final race begins at 12:24 p.m. MATT FARMER 
</P>
</TEXT>
