<HEADLINE>
<P>
MCALISTER RUNS HOOVER INTO THE GROUND, 42-3 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DARIN ESPER, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Pasadena quarterback Chris McAlister carried six times for 90 yards and two 
touchdowns and returned a punt 68 yards for a score to lead the Bulldogs to a 
42-3 rout of Hoover in the Pacific League opener Thursday night at Glendale 
High. 
</P>
<P>
 McAlister, a senior, ran 57 yards down the right sideline on a bootleg play 20 
seconds into the second quarter to open the scoring.He ran the same play for a 
21-yard score with 9 minutes 17 seconds left in the third quarter to put 
Pasadena (4-2) ahead, 21-0. 
</P>
<P>
 "I think our coaches had a good scheme to try and stop him," Hoover Coach 
Dennis Hughes said, "But he had other ideas. 
</P>
<P>
 "You can't really stop a guy like that anyways, just try to contain him. We 
were in the right place to do that, but he had the athleticism to get into the 
open field." 
</P>
<P>
 Late in the first half, Pasadena linebacker Lester Town twice stopped 
ballcarriers for losses, forced a fumble, and blocked a 50-yard field-goal 
attempt by Marco Mesrobian with 1:51 left. 
</P>
<P>
 Hoover (2-4) avoided a shutout when Mesrobian kicked a 31-yard field goal with 
7:01 to play. Emre Ozgur gained 83 yards in 19 carries for Hoover. 
</P>
