<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL ROUNDUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In another cross-country meet: 
</P>
<P>
 Foothill League Meet No. 2 -- The Hart boys' and girls' teams remained 
undefeated in league competition in the meet at Griffith Park. 
</P>
<P>
 Brett Strahan won his fourth race of the season -- against one loss -- with a 
time of 15:19 in the boys' race as the Indians (8-0, 8-0) placed seven runners 
among the top 10 finishers. 
</P>
<P>
 Joel Givens (15:50), John Duarte (15:53) and Sandro Soler (16:10) placed 
second, third and fourth for Hart, which is shooting for its 12th consecutive 
league title. 
</P>
<P>
 The Indians placed five runners among the top 13 finishers in the girls' race, 
paced by sophomores Monica Prelle (fourth in 19:20) and Lisa Klinger (fifth in 
19:25). GIRLS' VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
<P>
 Newbury Park d. Camarillo, 15-4, 15-5, 15-9 -- Christine Arguijo had six kills 
and Julie Wastell added five to lead the Panthers to a Marmonte League victory 
at Newbury Park (9-1, 7-1). Setter Kari Norberg notched 23 assists. 
</P>
<P>
 Thousand Oaks d. Royal, 14-16, 15-13, 6-15, 15-7, 15-8 -- Kristin Scott had 14 
kills and 15 blocks and teammate Christy Stueve added 13 kills and 16 digs as 
the host Lancers (7-3, 6-2) came from behind in the Marmonte League match. 
Susan Torst had 18 kills for Royal (6-4, 5-3). 
</P>
<P>
 Simi Valley d. Westlake, 15-6, 15-10, 15-11 -- Kristin Sampson had eight kills 
and 19 digs to boost the host Pioneers (4-6, 3-5) in a Marmonte League match. 
Shelley Crandall added 15 assists. 
</P>
<P>
 Kennedy d. Taft 15-4, 15-1, 15-10 -- Tresa Moorman had 11 kills and Kelly 
Samuel added 10 for host Kennedy in a Northwest Valley Conference match. 
Stephanie Ong had 30 assists. 
</P>
<P>
 Bell-Jeff d. St. Anthony, 15-7, 15-4, 15-9 -- Letty Cabrera led the host 
Guards (10-2, 4-0) with 10 kills and 10 digs in a Camino Real League match. 
Lauren Barrett added seven kills, nine digs and four blocks. 
</P>
<P>
 St. Bonaventure d. Oak Park, 15-5, 15-2, 15-5 -- Kristin Klarc led the host 
Seraphs (9-1, 3-1) with 10 kills in the Tri-Valley League match. 
</P>
<P>
 Chatsworth d. Birmingham, 13-15, 15-8, 15-4, 15-9 -- Jennifer Joseph had 15 
kills and six aces to lead the host Chancellors (6-2, 5-0) in a matchup of 
teams that were previously unbeaten in the Northwest Valley Conference. 
</P>
<P>
 Marciela Valdez had 16 kills and Dinora Marroquin had 28 assists for the 
Braves (7-2, 4-1). GIRLS' TENNIS 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Barbara 13, Rio Mesa 5 -- The Dons' No. 3 singles player, Pilara 
Montgomery, swept her matches, including a 6-0 victory against Rio Mesa's 
Zuzana Stunova. Stunova beat Montgomery, 6-0, earlier this season. 
</P>
<P>
 Stunova won her other two singles matches, but it wasn't enough against the 
Channel League's top team. Santa Barbara is 8-0 in league. Rio Mesa is 7-4, 
5-3. 
</P>
<P>
 Burbank 15 1/3, Hart 5 2/3 -- Analisa Swan swept her singles matches to propel 
the Bulldogs (10-2, 5-0) in a Foothill League match. 
</P>
<P>
 Nordhoff 13, Carpinteria 5 -- Rangers singles players Stacey Roberts, Brianne 
Chapman and Haley Wilburn swept their three matches in the nonleague meeting at 
Carpinteria. Nordhoff is 6-3. 
</P>
<P>
 La Reina 16, Bishop Diego 2 -- Cindy Bear, Kristy Bear and Kristin Dickey 
swept their matches without losing a game. Host La Reina improved to 8-2, 5-0 
in the Tri-Valley League. 
</P>
<P>
 Chaminade 12, Flintridge Prep 6 -- Tina Kapadia swept all three of her singles 
matches to lead the host Eagles (10-2, 9-0) in a Mission League match. 
</P>
</TEXT>
