</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA101494-0125 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 088477 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
October 14, 1994, Friday, Ventura West Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Metro; Part B; Page 7; Column 1 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
625 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
CAMPAIGN CALENDAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Upcoming Events 
</P>
<P>
 Today: Cheryl Heitman, a candidate for the board of the Conejo Valley Unified 
School District, will hold two meet-the-candidate receptions at private homes 
in Thousand Oaks. The first is scheduled for 9:15 to 10:15 a.m., and the second 
11 a.m. to noon. For directions and information: 496-0049. 
</P>
<P>
 Today: Ekbal Quidwai, a candidate for the Thousand Oaks City Council, will 
hold a meet-the-candidate session at The Oaks mall, 222 W. Hillcrest Drive, 11 
a.m. to 2 p.m. Information: 378-7274. 
</P>
<P>
