<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: MID-CITY; BOY DIES, 
COMPANION SHOT IN APPARENT GANG ATTACK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A teen-age boy was shot to death Thursday and his companion seriously wounded 
on a sidewalk in the Mid-City area of Los Angeles after a carload of apparent 
gang members confronted them, shouted a challenge and then opened fire, police 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 The two youths, both 15, were attacked at 4:05 p.m. as they were walking on 
Queen Anne Place near Pico Boulevard, said Los Angeles Police Officer Edmund 
Rodriguez.One youth was shot in the head, shoulder and chest; the other was 
shot in the abdomen, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 Both boys were taken to a nearby hospital, where one died and the other 
remained in serious condition. Their names were not released by police. 
</P>
<P>
 Rodriguez said it was unclear what sparked the confrontation, but said it is 
being investigated by police gang specialists. The assailants left at least 10 
shell casings at the scene, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
