 30-Year Mortgage Rates Increase: Fixed-rate mortgages averaged 8.94% this 
week, up from 8.89% last week, according to a national survey released by the 
Federal Home Loan Mortgage Corp. It was the highest since April 3, 1992, when 
the average was 8.96%.The average hit a 25-year low of 6.74% in October. On 
one-year, adjustable-rate mortgages, lenders were asking an average initial 
