<P>
CONSUMER BRIEFS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Stereogram Books: Blue Mountain Press, publisher of alternative greeting 
cards, is introducing a series of books of 5-D stereograms, which are pictures 
that change to reveal hidden images. 
</P>
<P>
 The pages at first appear to be a series of blurry, multicolored images, but 
as the eye lingers, the images change to reveal a pictorial message. The series 
includes "Endangered Species in 5-D Stereograms," "Love in 5-D Stereograms" and 
"Reach for Your Dreams in 5-D Stereograms." 
</P>
<P>
 Five percent of the proceeds from the sale of "Endangered Species," which 
sells for $12.95, will be donated to Defenders of Wildlife, a group dedicated 
to the conservation of wildlife and natural habitats. 
</P>
<P>
 "Love in 5-D" and "Reach for Your Dreams" sell for $17.95. 
</P>
