<HEADLINE>
<P>
O.C. BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Parker Bertea Aerospace: Israel Aircraft Industries Ltd. has selected the 
Irvine firm to design and produce the horizontal stabilizer operating package 
for its new Astra Galaxy business jet. The value of the contract was not 
disclosed. 
</P>
<P>
 The two-speed system, called a trim actuator, will be built by Parker Bertea 
Aerospace Control Systems division in Irvine and installed in conjunction with 
an electronic controller built by Parker Bertea's Gull Electronic Systems 
Division in New York. 
</P>
<P>
 Israel Aircraft Industries estimates that between 140 and 220 Astra Galaxy 
jets will be built over the life of the program. The actuator is scheduled for 
delivery beginning in August. 
</P>
<P>
 Parker Bertea Aerospace designs, manufactures and services hydraulic, 
pneumatic and fuel components, systems and related electronic controls for 
aircraft, space and marine high-technology markets. It is a subsidiary of 
Cleveland-based Parker Hannifin Corp., a $2.6-billion maker of motion-control 
components and systems for the industrial and aerospace markets. 
</P>
