<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: THE WORKPLACE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Don Lee, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Lawsuit Settlement: Nearly two years after a big drywall workers' strike in 
Southern California, six carpenters' union groups involved in that labor 
dispute have agreed to make a "substantial payment" to settle a lawsuit filed 
by 11 San Diego contractors. 
</P>
<P>
 The suit, one of many traded by the unions and contractors, alleged various 
unfair labor practices against four carpenter locals and two of that union's 
umbrella groups. The five-month drywall strike, centered in Orange County, 
resulted in a victory for the workers, who won a contract with more than 50 
companies in Southern California. But not the 11 San Diego contractors. 
</P>
<P>
 The settlement was disclosed in a joint release by the union and contractors. 
Details were not released. 
</P>
</TEXT>
