<P>
EAST VALLEY FOCUS: SYLMAR; PARK OFFICIAL TO GIVE UPDATE ON PROJECTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TIM MAY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A city parks official will update residents on the status of major 
improvements scheduled or already under way at Sylmar Park, Stetson Ranch 
Equestrian Center and Hansen Dam Recreation Area at a meeting next week. 
</P>
<P>
 James Ward, principal grounds maintenance supervisor for the San Fernando 
Valley region, Los Angeles Department of Recreation and Parks, will speak to 
the Sylmar Coordinating Council at noon Wednesday at Mission College, Room 1, 
13356 Eldridge Ave. 
</P>
<P>
 Ward will discuss on-going work at the 28.8-acre undeveloped equestrian 
center. Improvements slated there include regrading the two riding arenas, 
installing fencing, repairing the staging/trailer lots and constructing an 
irrigation system to control dust. The center is scheduled to reopen March 29. 
</P>
<P>
 At Sylmar Park, two soccer fields will be ready for the spring season, and the 
park's new baseball fields, swimming pool and recreational building have been 
completed, Ward said. 
</P>
<P>
 And at Hansen Dam, a groundbreaking ceremony for the new 1.5-acre swimming 
lake has been scheduled for Oct. 26.TIM MAY 
