<HEADLINE>
<P>
CAMPAIGN CALENDAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Annette Hall, president of the League of Women Voters of Los Angeles, will 
discuss issues on the Nov. 8 ballot at a meeting of B'nai B'rith Women Tikvah 
chapter at 7 p.m. Wednesday at the Fallbrook Mall's Meeting Place, 6633 
Fallbrook Ave., West Hills. Admission is free.Information: (818) 591-1436. 
</P>
<P>
 * Arguments for and against Proposition 187, the anti-illegal immigration 
initiative, will be presented at 7:30 p.m. Wednesday at Woodland Hills 
Community Church, 21338 Dumetz Road. Information: (818) 346-0820. 
</P>
<P>
 * A candidates forum will be held at 7 p.m. Thursday at Temple Judea, 5429 
Lindley Ave., Tarzana. Candidates, or their representatives, for governor, U. 
S. Senate, 24th and 25th Congressional districts and the 41st Assembly District 
are expected to participate. Admission is free. Information: (818) 587-3203. 
</P>
