<HEADLINE>
<P>
FORMER UCI PLAYER BEERS FILES SUIT AGAINST SCHOOL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOHN WEYLER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Elizabeth Beers, a former basketball player at UC Irvine, filed suit Wednesday 
in Orange County Superior Court alleging the university medical staff 
misdiagnosed a back injury suffered during a game against Long Beach State on 
Feb. 23, 1992. 
</P>
<P>
 The suit alleges that trainer Loreen Koshi, who is no longer at the school, 
diagnosed the injury as a sprain -- despite swelling and numbness radiating 
down Beers' legs -- without the aid of a physician's examination.Beers was 
cleared nine days later to play in a game during which the injury was allegedly 
aggravated, eventually leading to spinal fusion surgery last December. 
</P>
<P>
 Because of ongoing medical treatment, a dollar figure has not been attached to 
the suit, according to attorney J. David Mazurek. Beers also is seeking damages 
because her scholarship was revoked this year, which the suit alleges violated 
a verbal agreement with the school. She received a reduced scholarship for the 
1993-94 academic year. 
</P>
<P>
 Irvine Athletic Director Dan Guererro said Thursday that he had not seen the 
suit and could not comment on pending litigation. JOHN WEYLER 
</P>
</TEXT>
